Detailed Description

Functions to convert from OBD output to actual values Functions declared in this file are named by their OBD Service command which is two hex digits. It's easier than coming up with short unique names myself. Please refer to obdservicecommands.h to see what's what.

Definition in file obdconvertfunctions.h.

typedef float(* OBDConvFunc)(unsigned int A, unsigned int B, unsigned int C, unsigned int D)

All obd conversion functions adhere to this.

Definition at line 36 of file obdconvertfunctions.h.

typedef int(* OBDConvRevFunc)(float val, unsigned int *A, unsigned int *B, unsigned int *C, unsigned int *D)

All obd reverse conversion functions adhere to this return value is number of values [A,B,C,D] filled.
